==English==

===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} '''[[ελληνίζειν]]''' (''hellenizein'') "to speak Greek, to make Greek, to become Greek", from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[Έλλην]]''' (''[[Hellen]]'') "Greek".

===Intransitive Verb===
{{en-verb|Helleniz|ing}}

# To use the language and culture of the ancient Greeks, to become [[Hellenistic]].
# To become Greek in character, language, culture, or civilization. 

===Transitive Verb===
{{en-verb|Helleniz|ing}}

# To make Greek in character, language, culture, or civilization.

